settings.label: Group ID
settings.description: The name of the consumer group to join for dynamic partition assignment (if enabled), and to use for fetching and committing offsets.

settings.name: bootstrap_servers
settings.label: Bootstrap Servers
settings.description: host[:port] string (or list of comma separated host[:port] strings) that the consumer should contact to bootstrap initial cluster metadata.

settings.name: primary_keys
settings.label: Primary Keys
settings.description: Optionally you can define primary key for the consumed messages. It requires a column name and /slashed/paths ala xpath selector to extract the value from the kafka messages. The extracted column will be added to every output singer message.

settings.name: use_message_key
settings.label: Use Message Key
settings.description: (Default true) Defines whether to use Kafka message key as a primary key for the record. Note - custom primary key(s) takes precedence if such defined and use_message_key is set to true.

settings.name: initial_start_time
settings.label: Initial Start Time
settings.description: (Default latest) Start time reference of the message consumption if no bookmarked position in state.sjon. One of - latest, earliest or an ISO-8601 formatted timestamp string.

settings.name: max_runtime_ms
settings.label: Max Runtime (ms)
settings.description: (Default 300000) The maximum time for the tap to collect new messages from Kafka topic. If this time exceeds it will flush the batch and close kafka connection.

settings.name: commit_interval_ms
settings.label: Commit Internal (ms)
settings.description: (Default 5000) Number of milliseconds between two commits. This is different than the kafka auto commit feature. Tap-kafka sends commit messages automatically but only when the data consumed successfully and persisted to local store.

settings.name: consumer_timeout_ms
settings.label: Consumer Timeout (ms)
settings.description: (Default 10000) KafkaConsumer setting. Number of milliseconds to block during message iteration before raising StopIteration

settings.name: session_timeout_ms
settings.label: Session Timeout (ms)
settings.description: (Default 30000) KafkaConsumer setting. The timeout used to detect failures when using Kafkas group management facilities.

settings.name: heartbeat_interval_ms
settings.label: Heartbeat Interval (ms)
settings.description: (Default 10000) KafkaConsumer setting. The expected time in milliseconds between heartbeats to the consumer coordinator when using Kafkas group management facilities.

settings.name: max_poll_records
settings.label: Max Poll Records
settings.description: (Default 500) KafkaConsumer setting. Maximum number of records to poll.

settings.name: max_poll_interval_ms
settings.label: Max Poll Interval (ms)
settings.description: (Default 300000) KafkaConsumer setting. The maximum delay between invocations of poll() when using consumer group management.

settings.name: message_format
settings.label: Message Format
settings.description: (Default json) Supported message formats are json and protobuf.

settings.name: proto_schema
settings.label: Protobuf Schema
settings.description: Protobuf message format in .proto syntax. Required if the message_format is protobuf.

settings.name: proto_classes_dir
settings.label: Protobuf Classes Directory
settings.description: (Default current working dir)
